<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="zh-CN">
<head><title>AI Web FTP — Agent Skill Reference</title>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
  :root{--primary:#2563eb;--bg:#f8fafc;--card:#fff;--border:#e2e8f0;--text:#1e293b;--muted:#64748b}
  *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
  body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,sans-serif;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);padding:24px}
  .container{max-width:860px;margin:0 auto}
  .card{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:10px;padding:28px 32px}
  h2{font-size:20px;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:4px}
  .subtitle{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:14px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}
  h3{font-size:15px;font-weight:600;margin-top:28px;margin-bottom:10px;color:var(--primary);padding-bottom:4px;border-bottom:1px solid #f0f0f0}
  h4{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:6px}
  p{font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:8px}
  code{background:#f1f5f9;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:13px}
  pre{background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;padding:14px;overflow-x:auto;font-size:13px;line-height:1.6;margin:8px 0 16px}
  table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:13px;margin:8px 0 16px}
  th,td{border:1px solid var(--border);padding:7px 10px;text-align:left}
  th{background:#f8fafc;font-weight:600}
  ul,ol{margin:6px 0 14px;padding-left:20px}
  li{font-size:14px;line-height:1.8}
  .tag{display:inline-block;padding:1px 8px;border-radius:10px;font-size:11px;font-weight:600}
  .tag-get{background:#dbeafe;color:#1d4ed8}
  .tag-put{background:#fef3c7;color:#b45309}
  .tag-post{background:#bbf7d0;color:#15803d}
  .tag-del{background:#fca5a5;color:#b91c1c}
  .nl{margin-top:24px;padding-top:16px;border-top:1px solid var(--border)}
  .nl a{color:var(--primary);text-decoration:none;font-size:13px}
  .nl a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
</style></head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>AI Web FTP &mdash; Agent Skill Reference</h2>
      <p class="subtitle">HTTP-based file service for LLM agents. Full CRUD via GET-only queries. Only one operation per request.</p>

      <h3>Overview</h3>
      <p>AI Web FTP exposes remote file operations as simple HTTP requests. Agents limited to <strong>GET-only</strong> (no headers, no body) can still create, read, update, and delete files using query parameters.</p>

      <h3>When to Use</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Your agent needs to <strong>read</strong> files or list directories</li>
        <li>Your agent needs to <strong>write/upload</strong> files</li>
        <li>Your agent needs to <strong>delete</strong> or <strong>rename</strong> files remotely</li>
        <li>Your agent is <strong>limited to GET requests</strong> only</li>
        <li>Your agent needs to <strong>check permissions</strong> before acting</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;"><em>Do NOT use for:</em> real-time sync, WebDAV, or multi-user auth beyond a shared access key.</p>

      <h3>Core Pattern</h3>
      <p>All requests target <code>/s/{path}?key=xxx</code>. The <code>path</code> maps to a virtual directory on the server. Specialized tools are under <code>/tool/</code>.</p>
      <pre>GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx                # Read file or list directory
GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx&mkdir=1        # Create directory
GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx&upload_url=URL # Upload from URL
GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx&content=...    # Upload text content
GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx&delete=1       # Delete file or empty dir
GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx&rename_to=NEW  # Rename
GET  /s/{path}?key=xxx&move_to=/DEST  # Move
GET  /tool/edit?path=...&key=xxx&old_str=...&new_str=...  # Edit text file</pre>
      <p>Agents supporting other HTTP methods:</p>
      <pre>PUT   /s/{path}?key=xxx               # Upload raw body as file
POST  /s/{path}?key=xxx               # Upload multipart file
POST  /s/{path}?key=xxx&mkdir=1       # Create directory
DELETE /s/{path}?key=xxx              # Delete file or empty dir</pre>

      {% if level!="basic" %}
      <h3>Quick Reference</h3>

      <h4>Permissions</h4>
      <p>Query your access level:</p>
      <pre>GET /perm/{path}?key=xxx</pre>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Permission</th><th>Operation</th><th>Effect</th></tr>
        <tr><td><code>list</code></td><td>GET directory</td><td>Returns file listing</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>read</code></td><td>GET file</td><td>Returns content or download</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>write</code></td><td>POST/PUT upload, mkdir</td><td>Creates files and directories</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>delete</code></td><td>GET/DELETE &amp; delete=1</td><td>Removes files or empty dirs</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>rename</code></td><td>GET &amp; rename_to/move_to</td><td>Renames or moves items</td></tr>
      </table>

      <h4>Common Parameters</h4>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Param</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        <tr><td><code>key</code></td><td>string</td><td>Access key (required)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>json</code></td><td>0/1</td><td>Return JSON instead of HTML</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>raw</code></td><td>0/1</td><td>Raw file content as text</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>download</code></td><td>0/1</td><td>Force file download</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>help</code></td><td>string</td><td>Attach docs: basic, full, md</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>filename</code></td><td>string</td><td>Override upload filename</td></tr>
      </table>

      <h4>Security Constraints</h4>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Constraint</th><th>Limit</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Max upload size</td><td>500 MB</td></tr>
        <tr><td>content= param max</td><td>64 KB</td></tr>
        <tr><td>upload_url protocol</td><td>HTTPS only</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Destination</td><td>Public internet only (no private IPs)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Write rate limit</td><td>60 ops/minute</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Path traversal</td><td>Blocked (realpath + normcase)</td></tr>
      </table>

      <h3>Usage Patterns</h3>

      <h4>1. Read a file (GET-only agent)</h4>
      <pre>GET /s/data/readme.txt?key=abc123</pre>
      <p>Returns HTML with preview. Add <code>&json=1</code>:</p>
      <pre>GET /s/data/readme.txt?key=abc123&amp;json=1
&rarr; {"type":"file","filename":"readme.txt","size":1024,...}</pre>

      <h4>2. Upload from URL (GET-only)</h4>
      <pre>GET /s/data/uploads?key=abc123&amp;upload_url=https://example.com/file.zip</pre>
      <p>Override filename with <code>&amp;filename=out.zip</code>:</p>
      <pre>GET /s/data/uploads?key=abc123&amp;upload_url=https://example.com/download&amp;filename=package.zip</pre>

      <h4>3. Upload text content (GET-only)</h4>
      <pre>GET /s/data/notes/hello.txt?key=abc123&amp;content=Hello+World</pre>

      <h4>4. Upload binary (agent with PUT)</h4>
      <pre>PUT /s/data/image.jpg?key=abc123
Content-Type: application/octet-stream

&lt;binary data&gt;</pre>

      <h4>5. Create dir + upload</h4>
      <pre>GET /s/data/newproject?key=abc123&amp;mkdir=1
GET /s/data/newproject/main.py?key=abc123&amp;content=print("hello")</pre>

      <h4>6. Edit text file (precision replace)</h4>
      <pre>GET /tool/edit?path=/data/config.json&amp;key=abc123&amp;old_str=debug%3Atrue&amp;new_str=debug%3Afalse
GET /tool/edit?path=/data/README.md&amp;key=abc123&amp;old_str=v1.0&amp;new_str=v2.0&amp;replace_all=1</pre>


      <h3>Error Handling</h3>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
        <tr><td>400</td><td>Bad request (invalid params, filename)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>403</td><td>Access denied (wrong key, no permission)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>404</td><td>Share or path not found</td></tr>
        <tr><td>409</td><td>Conflict (exists, dir not empty)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>413</td><td>Payload too large</td></tr>
        <tr><td>429</td><td>Rate limited</td></tr>
        <tr><td>507</td><td>Insufficient storage</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p>With <code>?json=1</code>: <code>{"success":false,"error":"...","code":N}</code></p>

      <h3>Common Mistakes</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Conflicting parameters</strong> &mdash; Only one operation per request. <code>mkdir=1&amp;delete=1</code> returns 400.</li>
        <li><strong>Missing trailing slash</strong> &mdash; <code>/s/test?key=abc</code> and <code>/s/test/?key=abc</code> both work</li>
        <li><strong>Cross-share move</strong> &mdash; Moving files between different shares is rejected with 403</li>
        <li><strong>Delete non-empty dir</strong> &mdash; Must delete contents first (returns 409)</li>
        <li><strong>Rename over existing</strong> &mdash; Fails with 409 if target already exists</li>
      </ul>
      {% endif %}

